char c; // variable c stores a character

#include <stdio.h>

int main(){
    printf("%d\n", sizeof(char));
}
/* Output:
1

*/

char c = 'x'; // variable c receives the character 'x' and stores it
char c = x; // variable c receives the value stored in variable x

Se x representar um valor númerico definido, char c, receberá  o valor ao qual ele guardou. 


char c = 65; // variable c is given the value 'A'



#include <stdio.h>

int main(){
    char x;

    x = getchar(); // variable x receives the value of the character typed by the user

    putchar(x); // the value of the variable x eh printed
}
